## Hardened APT Configuration

## 1. Network & Auth Security
## Force strict chain verification
Acquire::https::Verify-Peer "true";
Acquire::https::Verify-Host "true";

## Never allow unauthenticated packages
APT::Get::AllowUnauthenticated "false";
Acquire::AllowInsecureRepositories "false";
Acquire::AllowDowngradeToInsecureRepositories "false";

## 2. Sandbox & Isolation
## Use seccomp sandbox for apt methods to limit syscalls
# APT::Sandbox::Seccomp "true";

## Drop privileges to '_apt' user for downloading
APT::Sandbox::User "_apt";

## 3. Supply Chain / Integrity
## Do not use PDiffs, always download full indices for integrity
Acquire::PDiffs "false";
Acquire::IndexTargets::deb::Header "Signed-By";

## 4. Cleanup
## Do not keep local copies of downloaded debs
APT::Keep-Downloaded-Packages "false";
APT::Clean-Installed "true";
